.TH "ep_write_UDCCSR" 9 "ep_write_UDCCSR" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ep_write_UDCCSR \- set bits in UDCCSR
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ep_write_UDCCSR
.BI "(struct pxa_ep *ep "  ","
.BI "int mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ep" 12
udc endpoint
.IP "mask" 12
bits to set in UDCCR
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Sets bits in UDCCSR (UDCCSR0 and UDCCSR*).

A specific case is applied to ep0 : the ACM bit is always set to 1, for
SET_INTERFACE and SET_CONFIGURATION.
